          'Insoluble — does not diffuse out of cells and does not affect water potential or osmosis',
          'Compact — starch molecules can fold up tightly, fitting into small storage organelles (e.g. starch grains in potato tuber cells)',
          'Can be rapidly synthesised and broken down — plants have enzymes to do this quickly',
          'Amylase (a digestive enzyme) hydrolyses starch → maltose; maltose is then hydrolysed → glucose for respiration',
          'Stored in seeds and storage organs (bulbs, tubers) as long-term energy reserve; also used for short-term storage overnight when photosynthesis cannot occur',
